Others: The NBA released its Last Two Minute Report for the New York Knicks' Friday night game against the Brooklyn Nets, which was marked by controversy over officiating.
The report determined that the referees did not make any mistakes in the final two minutes of the game, suggesting that this Knicks win was clean.
The game was chippy, with a shoving match between Dorian Finney-Smith and OG Anunoby.
One of the most notable calls in question was when Nets guard Dennis Schroder attacked the basket with less than 30 seconds in the game and met Knicks center Ariel Hukporti.
